âš™ï¸ Pre-Exploitation â€” Weaponization & Gaining Initial Access
Pre-exploitation is the often-overlooked bridge between reconnaissance and full exploitation. Itâ€™s where information becomes actionable. In the CPTS exam, this is where youâ€™ll spend a good chunk of time validating assumptions, crafting payloads, testing footholds, and preparing the foundation for lateral movement.

The exam doesnâ€™t hand you vulnerable boxes with obvious paths. Instead, it expects you to assemble the pieces from recon and translate them into a valid, stable, and stealthy point of entry. This stage is also critical for payload delivery, shell handling, and execution strategies.

